Such systems of conditions are called as bootstrap equations. They
represent nontrivial relations between the resonance parameters
(pole positions and residue values) of the function under
consideration. In the present example the pole position does not
depend on the cross-channel variable. In this case the system of
bootstrap equations leads to  an infinite set of relations for the
values of residues (Pochhammer symbols).

